sourceMeaningMnemonic: What kind of <radical>fish</radical> jumps from <radical>dirt</radical> to <radical>dirt</radical>? A <kanji>salmon</kanji>!
meaningInfo: When you're at the river watching salmon jumping up stream, they keep jumping onto the dirt, flopping back into the water, then doing it again.
readingMnemonic: You make a drinking game out of watching the <kanji>salmon</kanji> going up stream. Every time one jumps onto the dirt, you drink a shot of <reading><ja>酒</ja></reading> (<ja>さけ</ja>). You realize you're drunk when you ask for more <ja>さけ</ja> but it comes out as <reading><ja>しゃけ</ja></reading>.
readingInfo:
Salmon. Drink <ja>さけ</ja>. Salmon. Drink <ja>さけ</ja>. Salmon. Drink...

"Ughhh.... I'm feeling tipsy... Hey, where's my <ja>しゃけ</ja>!?"
